‚ÄòThe Lines We Crossed‚Äô short film üé¨

A raw and tender story of found family, the messiness of healing, and the unexpected power of being seen. Three lives, stitched together by loneliness, come alive in the light of connection - and in that light, hope can take root where none was meant to grow.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Secondary role: Mrs Habib, Deva's mother, was once warm and loving, but grief has reshaped her. She struggles to see her son as she once did and can no longer be the nurturing presence he longs for. Her heart turned stone cold, after the death of her only daughter, she now suppresses her maternal instincts.

Female
30-55 years
Middle Eastern heritage

Shooting date: 08/12/2025
Location: London
Unpaid, festival exposure & portfolio content 

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Secondary role: Mrs. Kane is dramatic, flirty, and unapologetically over-the-top, with a flair for gossip and a love of all things a little chavvy. While she loves both of her children, her eldest, Cody, is clearly the favorite - her pride and joy - often leaving Keira to fend for herself. Mrs. Kane desperately clings to Cody's success, seeing it as her ticket to status and financial security.

Female
30-55 years
White/Caucasian
London Accent

Shooting date: 06/12/2025
Location: London
Unpaid, festival exposure & portfolio content

Male
50-70 years
White/Caucasian

Unpaid, festival exposure & portfolio content

Looking forward to hearing from you!

DRAMA SHORT FILM CASTING CALL ‚Äì In His Care

SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Rose, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother‚Äôs new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Rose see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Rose. 

Wanted: 1 actor (M)for exciting new short film ‚ÄòIn His Care‚Äô. Shooting in HATFIELD, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- HARRY (Male, 35 - 50)

- Description: Mid 30s to 50

Harry is carer to Ruth, conniving and manipulative; calculated and dominating. He knows what he wants and how to get it. He isn‚Äôt a smart perpetrator but rather simple-minded praying on those who can‚Äôt defend themselves and has no one to defend them. He has been getting away with it until a young girl with a fiery soul starts to uncover his secret.

Height: Tall (6ft approx.)

- Appearance: Harry is a seemingly ordinary guy on the outside. Charismatic, confident, tall, handsome, well kept. If you walked past him down the street, he may smile or wink at you. He uses his looks and caring fa√ßade as leverage.

- Travel expenses and food covered

If you‚Äôre interested, please submit showreels and any enquiries to dylanturner1501@gmail.com

items.text:
Hallo Schauspieler:innen!
Das neue Jahr steht vor der T√ºr ‚Äì und damit auch eine neue Casting-Saison. Zeit f√ºr frische Headshots!

Warum ich? Ich bin selbst Schauspieler und habe w√§hrend meiner Ausbildung in London bei einer Casting Director gearbeitet. Dort habe ich genau gelernt, worauf Casting Directors und Agenturen bei Headshots wirklich achten.

All dieses Wissen lasse ich in meine Shootings einflie√üen ‚Äì damit eure Fotos die bestm√∂glichen Chancen haben.

Hier ist mein Angebot! Schaut es euch an und schreibt mir, damit wir euren Termin festlegen k√∂nnen. Wir k√∂nnen vorher auch einen kurzen Call machen: Ich gebe euch eine kleine Beratung dazu, wie ihr euch vorbereitet und was ihr zum Shooting mitbringen solltet, damit wir das Maximum aus unserer Zeit herausholen.

Also, lasst uns sprechen!

@jonjon_st
[www.jonjonstudio.com](http://www.jonjonstudio.com/)

üö® OPEN AUDITION ALERT - CHILD & ADULTS! 

üé∏ Majestic Productions Group presents

Andrew Lloyd Webber‚Äôs amateur production of SCHOOL OF ROCK üé∏

üìç Storyhouse Theatre, Chester

üìÖ Performances from 10th August 2026

üé§ ARE YOU READY TO ROCK THE STAGE?

Dewey Finn and his class of straight-A students are ready to plug in, turn up, and bring the house down and we want YOU in the band!

üëß CHILD & YOUTH CAST (AGES 11‚Äì21)

üé∂ We‚Äôre looking for musical and acting talent to fill student roles and ensemble parts.

üé∏ Some roles require instruments, guitar, bass, drums, or keyboard.

üé§ You must also be ready to sing, act, and move with energy!

üßë‚Äçüé§ ADULT CAST (18+)

üî• Seeking strong singers, actors, and comedians for principal and ensemble roles.

Casting all roles, male/ female, ages 16 to the skys the limit. Established theatre company, this is our 20th anniversary show.  Feel free to DM with any questions  :) We love to welcome both new and returning faces. https://www.facebook.com/sdevonplayers/posts/pfbid02ZMa7eMczWfS2sLuMyC9PS8D3niF9sNrBas3AaAjveVKDRfS6i9jMEATiKDWV9S85l

pageName.name: The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

user.name: The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

sharedPost.text:
While we are on tour for our current production of Jekyll & Hyde, we are also working behind the scenes on the early stages of the next. 
Today, we finished the first draft of our in-house script adaptation of the classic period adventure drama The Scarlet Pimpernel, set betwen England and France at the height of the French Revolution, which will be our 20th anniversary show and, as well as our usual regional touring, this will also be also our London theatre debut. 
The audition sides and packs will be on our website from the start of December - here is a quick peek at the draft opening speech, which also gives a good idea of the drama coming up later in the play! 
As always, we will be welcoming returning faces and new faces alike, and would also love to hear from people interested in being involved behind the scenes. 

As soon as the audition packs and sides are on our website, we will be announcing on all our socials and website, so keep an eye out :)

items.text:
# **Casting Call ‚Äî Student Film**

**Currently casting for a student final project film, shooting in January-February 2026.**

We‚Äôre currently looking for three actors for a student short film: two male (playing age 18-24) and one female (playing age 18-24).

No other physical features required, so open to all.

Please send showreel links and recent headshots to **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk** ‚Äî along with any other additional materials you want us to see.

Closing date is December 5th, as shooting begins in the new year. Must live near or be happy to travel to London among various locations, with travel and food fully covered.

## More Information

**Synopsis**

When Elias, a forlorn cinema clerk, encounters a mysterious figure who claims to know him, the pair embark on an emotional odyssey through memory and illusion. As the line between past and present fractures, and the distinction between the real and the surreal becomes ever-more blurred, Elias must confront the truths he‚Äôs long avoided ‚Äî and the self he‚Äôs tried to forget.

**Character overview: ELIAS**

Male, early 20s. Elias works in a cinema, struggling to come to terms with a recent emotional loss. He is slightly self-pitying, but becomes a serious, grounded character by the end.

**Character overview: LUCID**

Male, early 20s. Lucid is Elias‚Äô emotional foil: extroverted, while compassionate and mysterious.

**Character overview: ISOBELLA**

Female, early 20s. She is Elias‚Äô recent emotional loss. The whole story revolves around her, but she has minimal actual dialogue. She is a bit of a closed book, and could be played in a few ways.

**Shooting Dates**

Shooting dates to be confirmed, but will be between January and February 2026. Must be available within that window, but dates will be decided based on cast and crew availability within this time.

**Shooting Locations**

Various, including Kent, Buckinghamshire, and London.

**Expenses**

Travel and food will be provided, along with accommodation if necessary.

**Contact us**

To register your interest, please email **casting@desktopstudios.co.uk**. Please include any relevant information and links, such as showreels, headshots, and/or previous experience. No previous experience is required, but you must be able to showcase your abilities.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT FILM ‚ÄúTHE SCAM‚Äù (Expenses Paid)**

After a series of slick sales calls, a retired man is moments away from transferring his life savings to an investment ‚Äúadvisor‚Äù he‚Äôs never met. But when a sudden internet outage interrupts the transaction, the pause shatters the illusion ‚Äî forcing him to confront truth, desperation, and the human cost of manipulation.

Casting For:

**Peter (55 ‚Äì70)** ‚Äì male, well spoken

**Young Peter (25‚Äì35)** ‚Äì male, well spoken

**Peter‚Äôs Son (20‚Äì30)** ‚Äì male, techy/geeky

**Evelyn (50‚Äì70)** ‚Äì female, well spoken

**John/Simon (45‚Äì60)** ‚Äì male, accents preferred

**Location:** Around Sutton, Surrey
**Auditions:** Closing date for submissions - 6th December 2025
**Shoot:** January 2026
**Paid:** Expenses only (travel + food)
**Genre:** Suspense / dark comedy-drama

Further information: https://suttonfilm.co.uk/script/the-scam/

To apply: https://suttonfilm.co.uk/casting-call/

Any questions? - please PM me.

***COMMERCIAL CASTING CALL***

We‚Äôre looking for real dads with adult children separated by distance (different country, university etc.) who connect over their love of football for a commercial.

The commercial will be shooting for one day during 10 - 12 December in London. This is a paid opportunity (¬£750 per person) with no former acting experience needed to apply. Talent must be willing to share family photos and be comfortable with small crew to film inside their home for final scene.

Please apply ASAP with full names, ages, selfie and short intro about relationship and love of football to: hello@mcauleycasting.com with the subject ‚ÄòFootball Family‚Äô

LEAD ROLE: CLASSICALLY-TRAINED ACTOR WANTED (LONDON)

early December Shoot (date tbd)

To play the villain in an Intense Crime Drama short.

Description: Male, White, playing age 25 - 35, Athletic, 5'10+, 80 kg+, with experience playing strong character roles on stage or screen.

¬£300 for 1-Day-Shoot plus half a day of rehearsals.

Please send in a cover letter with your resume with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworks@gmail.com Please do not respond in the comments or via DM.

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR LATINO OR HISPANIC PEOPLE
For upcoming Non-Union Series, ANCIENT BODIES SEASON 2.

Looking for:
 
Latino or Hispanic People, all genders and Ages, and specifically:

- 1 x Latino and Hispanic, Female, Age 20-30 with Dark Brown Hair
- 1 x Latino and Hispanic Male, Age 35-40

Non-Union Actors Only
Rate: $200 per Day Flat
Manitoba Residents Only  
MUST HAVE SIN #: Canadian Citizen or Permanent Resident or have a Valid Work Permit (No Student Permits with no SIN number)

Where: Winnipeg and the surrounding areas, Manitoba

Dates: December 11th to 12th,  December 16-19th, 2025 

Please email info@oafilmstudio.com with the subject line of the role you‚Äôre sending in for - YOUR NAME

Send the following info:
- Full Name
- Age
- Gender
- Ethnicity
- Height
- Phone
- Email Address
- State that you are non-union and a Manitoba resident 
- State if you are a Canadian Citizen, or Permanent Resident (PR), or have a Valid Work Permit? (Not a student Permit or work permit, still being processed)
- Your availability from December 11th to 12th and  December 16-19, 2025 (Must be available all day and evening)
- Confirm if you have no Tattoos or not
- Do you have your own transportation or a reliable ride?
- If you have any acting or performance experience, let us know (Speaking, SOC, Background, Theatre, Public speaking, Social Media). No experience is alright.

- 2 Current (TAKEN DAY OF SUBMISSION) Photos (1 selfie & 1 Full Body Shot)

Please share!

#Winnipeg #winnipegcastingcall #WinnipegActing
Onalee Ames Film Studio 
150 Stafford, Winnipeg, MB

items.text: Episode 39 of Beyond Reel Talk podcast is here. Natalia Kostrzewa is a Polish-born actress who moved to Ireland before building her career in the UK. In this episode, she talks about her early life, training, and the realities Eastern European actors face in the UK. We also discuss self-tapes, casting pressure, social media, and staying grounded through rejection. She talks about her work at Owning It Acting Studio, her experiences on Black Mirror, and shares practical advice on showreels, headshots, nerves, and finding a life balance.

items.text:
Accommodation + Food + Drinks + free Parking Provided 

Own Gear Required  

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm looking for a Gaffer to join the crew of my upcoming independent short film Restless Mind, shooting 5th‚Äì9th January 2026 around Widemouth Bay and Tamar Lake (near Bude) in Cornwall, South West UK.

Our original gaffer has had to step away due to scheduling, but they‚Äôre kindly providing a handover, including location photos, videos, lighting notes, and floor-plan drawings, so you won‚Äôt be coming in blind.

ABOUT THE FILM:  

Restless Mind is a grounded, emotional drama centred on men‚Äôs mental health, grief, and the importance of talking. It‚Äôs a passion project with a dedicated crew who‚Äôve been deep in pre-production for months.

LOOKING FOR:  

‚Ä¢ A gaffer with previous experience  

‚Ä¢ Own lighting gear is essential  

‚Ä¢ Comfortable working on location with a small, passionate team  

‚Ä¢ Someone who values meaningful storytelling and collaborative filmmaking  

WHAT WE PROVIDE:

‚Ä¢ Free accommodation for all shoot days in Cornwall. (The filming house will be used as accommodation for the entire crew). 

‚Ä¢ Food and drinks provided daily (lunch and warm dinners after filming) 

‚Ä¢ Free on-site parking for the entire shoot  

‚Ä¢ A handover from the previous gaffer (locations, notes, diagrams, footage)  

‚Ä¢ A supportive, friendly, well-organised crew environment  

‚Ä¢ A chance to work on a heartfelt project highlighting an important topic  

‚Ä¢Due to this film being a micro budget film, budget is small, however I do want to meet an agreement that works for both parties involved. 

If you‚Äôre interested or want to hear more, please send me a private message. I‚Äôd love to see some samples of your previous work and arrange a call to chat about the project.

Thanks so much!  

Callum

‚ú® Free Try-it VIRTUAL Voice Lessons + 40% Off Your First Month! (Black Friday Special!) ‚ú®

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm Colleen, a voice & piano teacher and mompreneur, the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We have an amazing team of supportive, talented teachers who work with students of all ages and experience levels. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, looking to build technique, or just getting started, we welcome you to join us! 

For Black Friday, we‚Äôre offering 40% off your first month of lessons (4 lessons!)Your first lesson is completely free to try before making any commitment. If you decide to continue, that free lesson will count toward your discounted month. 

We offer lessons in voice, piano, violin, viola, cello, guitar, and acting, taught virtual via Zoom! 

If you‚Äôd like to try a free lesson, you can sign up here:  [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

DM me if you have any questions!

Acting in Longer Form ‚Äì with Arek Ziƒôtek

Ready to take your acting and improv to the next level and bring real stories to life on stage? This workshop is all about longer scenes, deeper characters, and authentic storytelling, guided by Arek Ziƒôtek, one of Warsaw‚Äôs most respected theatre improvisers and teachers.

Arek has worked with Keith Johnstone, the father of modern improvisation, and now he‚Äôs sharing that knowledge in this unique advanced workshop for experienced performers.

You‚Äôll explore long-form improvisation techniques, learn to build emotional depth in your characters, and discover how to create stories that feel real, funny, and moving, all in English.

üëâ Important: This is not for beginners. You‚Äôll need some previous acting or improv experience and a confident level of English. We‚Äôre keeping the group small so everyone gets space, feedback, and focus.

Why join?
‚ú® Learn from one of Poland‚Äôs top improv teachers.
‚ú® Master storytelling through longer scenes and strong relationships.
‚ú® Work in English with passionate, international performers.
‚ú® Grow your stage presence and confidence in a supportive circle.

Schedule & Pricing
üìÜ Starting: Tuesday, November 25th
‚è∞ 7:00 PM
üìç Atlas Tower ‚Äì al. Jerozolimskie 123A, Warsaw

üéüÔ∏è Limited Spots:
First 5 applicants: 300 PLN (full 4-week course)
Next 5 spots: 350 PLN

If more than 10 apply, we might open a second group, but no promises!

Join us for a deep, fun, and creative exploration of what it means to truly act and improvise in longer form.

2 DATS LEFT RSVP --->  https://forms.gle/GhutENbwc6vpXBLm9

We are giving rising talent their flowers. The Viral Stars & Honors Soir√©e is coming, and we are celebrating actors and digital creators who didn‚Äôt just go viral, but made real impact with 100K+ views and performances people could not scroll past.

This is not a regular industry mixer. It is a night of recognition, community, and opportunity with creators, actors, directors, casting contacts, marketing professionals, and digital storytellers all in one room. Expect real networking, genuine connection, a talent honors presentation, light bites, refreshments, karaoke, crystal giveaways, and the option to stay for a discounted murder mystery experience after 4 PM.

If you are looking to enter acting, grow as a creator, expand your network, or finally step into spaces that can open doors, this is your sign to show up.

Sunday, Nov 30 | 2‚Äì6 PM
Business Cocktail Attire
RSVP Required

message.text:
2 DAYS LEFT TO RSVP---> QR Code & LINK Below - YOU'RE INVITED THIS SUNDAY ü•ÇCelebrating the contributions of our actors and networking with other industry peers ‚Äì Flink Appreciation Event, November 30th @3pm (WestChase)

We‚Äôre officially in countdown mode‚Äîonly 2 days left to RSVP for the Viral Stars & Honors Soir√©e. We don‚Äôt want you to miss it, and we are finalizing our headcount, food, gifts, and seating now.

We're opening registration, and you're invited! Take a quick minute today to secure your spot using the link below:

RSVP Link: PAUSE QR CODE https://forms.gle/GhutENbwc6vpXBLm9

Bringing a friend or inviting a peer? Make sure they register as well. Every attendee needs their own RSVP so we can prepare properly and make sure everyone has the full experience.

We are celebrating viral talent that has surpassed 100K+ views and bringing together creators, performers, directors, casting professionals, and industry players for a night of connection and inspiration.

If you need help registering or want the link sent directly, just reply :

sydneejane@flinkbrandcoach.com #flinkhonors #flinkhouston #flinkusa #flinksoiree

items.summary:

We are giving rising talent their flowers. The Viral Stars & Honors Soir√©e is coming, and we are celebrating actors and digital creators who didn‚Äôt just go viral, but made real impact with 100K+ views and performances people could not scroll past.

This is not a regular industry mixer. It is a night of recognition, community, and opportunity with creators, actors, directors, casting contacts, marketing professionals, and digital storytellers all in one room. Expect real networking, genuine connection, a talent honors presentation, light bites, refreshments, karaoke, crystal giveaways, and the option to stay for a discounted murder mystery experience after 4 PM.

If you are looking to enter acting, grow as a creator, expand your network, or finally step into spaces that can open doors, this is your sign to show up.

Sunday, Nov 30 | 2‚Äì6 PM
Business Cocktail Attire
RSVP Required

items.text:
DAHLONEGA- Short Film- Auditions Open! 
Local Talent!
Unpaid-IMDB credited

Auditions happen NOW! for the first film of the season: ‚ÄúTHE SHAPE OF GOODBYE‚Äù

DEADLINE: Jan. 4th

An adaptation of the amazing play written by the talented John Mabey. 

All you have to do is email a video link of a 1-2 minute dramatic monologue to

fofingerfilmsauditions@gmail.com

Here is the Character list: 

MARCUS (30-45) stoic, disciplined, carrying unspoken grief
YOUNG MARCUS (17-21)- introspective, sensitive, with a youthful vulnerability
DUSTIN (45-60) - strong, confident, with a commanding presence
BOYFRIEND (17-21) - charming, caring, with a playful yet earnest demeanor
 HUSBAND (30-45) - loyal, contlicted, balancing love and responsibility
 MOTHER (35-45) - nurturing, resilient, emotionally grounded

Film summary 
THE SHAPE OF GOODBYE: 
FOLLOWS A FATHER AND SON
AS THEY STRUGGLE TO CONNECT
OF IN THEIR FRACTURED RELATIONSHIP ACROSS TIME. THROUGH GRIEF, LOVE AND HUMOR, THEY FIGHT THEIR WAY TOWARD HEALING AND TO EACH OTHER. AND WHAT THEY DISCOVER ALONG THE WAY FRACTURES
THE SHAPE OF TIME ITSELF AS MEMORIES
BECOME MANIFEST AND REVEAL UNSPOKEN TRUTHS.

FILMING DATES:

JAN. 31,FEB. 1st, and FEB, 7th and 8th
(subject to change)

WHERE: 
DAHLONEGA, GA

NON-PAID, IMDb CREDIT INCLUDED

Good luck! Message if you have any questions. We will gladly help you!

FO FINGER FILMS.

items.text:
Role Type: Supporting Gender: Male Age Range: Early to mid-20s Ethnicity: African American Build: Tall, physically imposing preferred

 Character Description:

 Dre is loud, cocky, and always looking to prove himself ‚Äî even when no one‚Äôs watching. He‚Äôs the type to stir the pot just for the reaction. A natural bully with a chip on his shoulder, Gangster Type. He‚Äôs a knucklehead with presence ‚Äî the guy you hear before you see. Seeking an actor with strong physicality and comedic or dramatic timing to bring Dre‚Äôs over-the-top bravado to life.

GRANDMA B Role Type: Supporting / Featured Gender: Female Age Range: Late 60s to 70s Ethnicity: African American, Mixed Race, or Hispanic Build: Average height and build.

 Character Description:

 Grandma B is the rock of the family ‚Äî wise, resilient, and sharp as ever. She speaks her mind with no filter and delivers truth with wit and love. Strong in her faith and unshakable in her values, she‚Äôs as quick with a Bible verse as she is with a one-liner. Whether offering tough love or quiet comfort, she‚Äôs always ten steps ahead. Looking for a seasoned actress who can bring warmth, sass, and soul to this memorable matriarch. 

 Roylina

Female25-40 y.o.

Latino / Hispanic

Character Description: 

Roylina is a powerful Mafia Boss‚Äîcommanding, strategic, and captivating. She carries herself with confidence, intensity, and an air of danger. The actress must be able to portray strength, authority, and emotional depth.

JACOB (JAY) -

Type: Principal

Gender: Male

Age Range: Early to mid-20s

Ethnicity: African American or Mixed Race

Complexion: Brown to Light

Build: Tall, athletic

 

Character Description:

Jacob (Jay) is confident, grounded, and carries a quiet strength. He‚Äôs sharp, emotionally mature beyond his years, and physically active. Jay‚Äôs presence is felt even in silence ‚Äì calm but commanding. His past has shaped him, but he doesn‚Äôt wear it on his sleeve. Looking for an actor who can bring both vulnerability and strength to the role with authenticity and nuance.

You‚Äôll be bringing these high-energy, magical characters to life at children‚Äôs parties, home visits, and special events

üé§ What‚Äôs Involved:

Performing as your assigned character (costumes & wigs provided)

Singing, dancing, and interacting with children

Hosting fun party games and activities

Creating unforgettable memories for kids!

CASTING CALL

As You Like It by William Shakespeare 
Directed by Bronwen Maeve and Hannah Scott

The Shakespeare All Year Theatre Society would love to encourage all to submit for our upcoming production of As You Like It set at a Renaissance Festival! The Bard‚Äôs enduring comedy brought to life in a Vancouver heritage building.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT FILM ‚ÄúTHE SCAM‚Äù (Expenses Paid)**

After a series of slick sales calls, a retired man is moments away from transferring his life savings to an investment ‚Äúadvisor‚Äù he‚Äôs never met. But when a sudden internet outage interrupts the transaction, the pause shatters the illusion ‚Äî forcing him to confront truth, desperation, and the human cost of manipulation.

Casting For:

**Peter (55 ‚Äì70)** ‚Äì male, well spoken

**Young Peter (25‚Äì35)** ‚Äì male, well spoken

**Peter‚Äôs Son (20‚Äì30)** ‚Äì male, techy/geeky

**Evelyn (50‚Äì70)** ‚Äì female, well spoken

**John/Simon (45‚Äì60)** ‚Äì male, accents preferred

items.text:
Role: Peter

 (Key Supporting ‚Äî Psychological Drama)

We are urgently seeking a London-based actor for a key supporting role in a tense psychological drama set inside a church.

Character Description:

‚Ä¢ Carries an undercurrent of grief, guilt, or restrained resentment

‚Ä¢ Able to shift subtly between controlled strength and quiet vulnerability

This is an unpaid test shoot created as part of a small scale  project. We are operating on a student budget, and while we cannot reliably cover full travel expenses, we will provide a ¬£10 contribution toward London Underground travel for all participating actors.

+++ ANGST vor Nichtbuchung bei Kritik +++

Ein heikles Thema, was immerwieder f√ºr Konflikte, aber  auch oft f√ºr Missverst√§ndnisse sorgt.

Dazu zwei typische Zitate aus unseren Kontakten:

"Ich hab da einmal wegen einer Zulage nachgefragt und dann abgesagt. Seitdem werde ich da nicht mehr gebucht."

"Ich frag da lieber nicht nach und mach den Dreh mit schlechter Gage, dann bekomm ich da auch wieder bessere  Sachen."

So, oder so √§hnlich h√∂ren wir ab und an  von Filmschaffenden  berichtet.

Obwohl es sich hierbei erstmal nur um  Ger√ºchte handelt f√§llt uns doch auf, dass sich der Glaube an diesse Konsequenz der Agenturen, Booker und Caster  (selbst im Bereich der einfachsten  Komparserie) sehr
verbreitet ist.

Dazu haben wir durch unsere √ºber 10-j√§hrige  Erfahrung und  Eure, uns vielen anvertrauten PN,s aber auch ganz einfach durch unsere vielen Beitrags-Statistiken ein  eindeutiges Ergebnis.

Die Angst, bereits nur bei sachlich, netter und geringf√ºgiger Kritik, nicht gebucht zu werden ist auch in unserem Arbeitsbereich Komparserie ein unbestrittener  Fakt und sehr verbreitet. 

Nur ein aktuelles Beispiel:

Unser letzter Beitrag zum  Unmut einer √§u√üerst gro√üen deutschen Produktionsst√§tte hatte auch eine besonders starke Leserschaft Jedoch sind die Reaktionen  unserer Leserschaft auf unserer Kritik und sogar unsere erzielten Erfolge bei  den gro√üen Playern wesenlich geringer als bei kleineren  Produktionen oder unseren allgemein geltenden  Artikeln.

Aber woher kommt diese sicherlich unbegr√ºndete Angst?

Dazu schauen wir in unsere unz√§hligen vertraulichen PNs, und auch dort ist immerwieder die Angst ein exorbitanter Faktor.
Dort und auch bei unseren Gespr√§chen an unseren Infost√§nden aber auch in den Aufenthaltsr√§umen der Drehorte h√∂rt man einen recht h√§ufigen Schlusssatz: 
"Aber Psst, sonst werde ich da nicht mehr gebucht"

Die pers√∂nlichen Erfahrungen unserer  Redaktion (Claudia und Klaus) aber auch von anderen, uns √∂ffentlich unterst√ºtzenden Filmschaffenden sprechen dagegen eine ganz andere Sprache.

Obwohl sehr viele  Produktionen und Agenturen unsere  √∂ffentliche Kritik und damit auch unsere Namen kennen, hatten wir dadurch nie das Problem einer Nichtbuchung zu beklagen. 

Dies erscheint uns auch als v√∂llig logisch, denn erfahrungsgem√§√ü haben Agenturen, Casting und Regie gar nicht die Zeit f√ºr eine zeitraubende Differenzierung zumindest im Bereich Komparserie aber auch bei Kleindarstellerrollen.

Das hei√üt nat√ºrlich, dass auch  wir   mal mit den Konditionen einer Produktion o. Agentur bez√ºglich unserer pers√∂nlichen Buchungen nicht immer ganz einig waren und daher auch einfach mal "nein" gesagt haben.

Daher k√∂nnen wir auch m√∂gliche systematisch angewendeten "schwarze Listen" aufgrund unserer umfangreichen Informationen, weitestgehend nicht best√§tigen. 
So hatten wir eigentlich nur in einem Fall  der Vergangenheit leider mehrere Hinweise darauf, dass bereits der Kontakt zu unserer Initiative zum  Ausschluss aus der Kartei f√ºhren w√ºrde. 

Wir hoffen aber, dass diese sehr traurigen, uns vorliegenden Drohungen aktuell dort und nat√ºrlich auch insgesamt nicht  praktiziert werden. Im Einzelfall gibt es sicherlich auch mal Konflikte, die jedoch im pers√∂nlichen und m√∂glichst freundlichen Austausch gel√∂st werden sollten.

Was wir letztendlich jedoch  nicht ausschlie√üen k√∂nnen, ist  eine andere Art der Nichtbuchung.
Diese ist gar nicht so selten und beschreibt der Fall und  einer  Bevorzugung eines sogenannten Komparsenpools, der zumindest  h√§ufigere Buchungen erf√§hrt  als Menschen, die vielleicht  nicht zum Kreis der √∂fter gebuchten Filmschaffenden geh√∂ren. 

Auch hier berichten uns jedoch z.B. die meisten Agenturen, dass hier keinesfalls die "alten Hasen" bevorzugt werden. 
Zudem handelt es sich beim Buchungsprocedere ja nur um mehrere Vorschl√§ge aus der Kartei, die der Regieassistenz  vorgelegt werden oder die Produktion hat bereits selbst den Zugriff auf die   Kartei. So bestimmt die eigentliche Auswahl der gebuchten Filmgesichter fast immer die Regieassistenz . 

Dazu geh√∂rt auch die oft sogenannte Stammkomparserie. Auch hier  entsteht oft der Eindruck einer Bevorzugung.
Dieser Umstand ist jedoch nachvollziebar, wenn eine √∂fter genutzte Hintergrund-Location einen Erkennungswert bei der Serienproduktion fordert (z.B. Dorfbewohner, Krankenhauspersonal, Polizeib√ºro oder auch die "Spusi-Chlique").

So k√∂nnen wir auch bez√ºglich unserer Erfahrungen,  nur immerwieder dazu appellieren, auch mehrfach wiederholte  Absagen nicht pers√∂nlich zu nehmen.

Nichtsdestotrotz wollen wir an dieser Stelle gern alle Agenturen und Produktionen freundlich bitten, auch weiterhin eine gesunde Mischung, alter wie neuer Gesichter der Regie vorzuschlagen um auch allen  Filmschaffenden m√∂glichst gleiche Buchungschancen zu gew√§hren. Insbesondere  bei einer der wenigen  Pay-Agenturen.

Abschlie√üend  k√∂nnen wir nur nochmal beruhigend res√ºmieren: 

+++ Bez√ºglich recht verbreiteter √Ñngste vor einer Nichtbuchung  sehen wir jedenfalls f√ºr unseren   Arbeitsbereich keinerlei Grund daf√ºr, sich mit sachlich und freundlich gef√ºhrter Kritik bei den Verantwortlichen oder eben via Faire Gagen zur√ºckzuhalten. Also nur Mut zur Kritik. Insgesamt gesehen haben wir da √ºberhaupt nichts zu verlieren. +++

Gerne nehmen wir dazu Eure Erfahrungen und Beispiele und damit nat√ºrlich auch die der Agenturen und Produktionen gleich hier oder via PN mit in die Diskussion.
 
Redaktion Faire Gagen

Casting Call!

We have one role left to cast!!

*Starchild* is a sci-fi drama that follows the story of two scientists, Vanessa and Tanner as they take separate paths to deal with their grief. Vanessa through faith, and Tanner through science. It's not until they discover the origins of life itself, that they reconcile to start a family of their own.

Looking to cast supporting character John Marlow.

The film is heartfelt, honest, and powerful.

Please send resume, headshot, and (if applicable) demo reel to starchildcasting@gmail.com

# **CASTING CALL (UPDATE)**

**WORKING LOVE STORY**
**UNTITLED LOVE STORY ‚Äì PROOF-OF-CONCEPT SHORT FILM**

**PAID PROJECT ‚Äì NASHVILLE, TN**

This is a 10-minute short/concept film exploring connection, conflict, and redemption.

We've received stunning and amazing submissions thus far.

But don't let that deter you, we're still seeking passionate actors ready to bring depth, chemistry, and authenticity to our lead role.

**Must be local to Nashville.**

## **LEAD ROLE STILL OPEN ‚Äî SCARLETT**

SCARLETT (Female/Any Ethnicity)

Age: Early‚Äìmid 30s

Occupation: Professional Dancer/Exotic

Character Type: Complex, layered, vulnerable yet resilient

Bio:

Scarlett has learned to walk the fine line between resilience and fragility. A professional dancer and Ten years sober, she‚Äôs proud of her progress but knows the shadows of her past still trail close behind. By day, she is a loving friend and loyal confidant, but by night she steps into the world of exotic dance, a job that pays her bills but keeps her tethered to old memories. She yearns for escape‚Äînot just from mediocrity, but from the quiet ache of loneliness. When Bryce unexpectedly enters her life, a deep love ignites both joy and absolute CHAOS. Together with her new found love, she navigates moments of beauty and heartbreak, FIGHTING to keep their love alive through the sobriety she‚Äôs fought so hard to hold on to.

(Interested persons should have a background in dance or experience dancing. Must be able to convey intense emotion and sexualized desire through dance performance. (NO NUDITY PLEASE!!!)

Hi, my name is Lyndon. 

I am a 21 year old 6ft4 male actor, singer, and impressionist.

I am looking for work doing any of the above, and I am also keen to do voiceovers. 

Please take a look/ listen to the reel below, which has a mix of the various things I love doing.

If you feel that you've got something that might suit me, then please get in touch via my  spotlight account where I have some more of my work. üôÇ

Ensemblet medvirker l√∏bende i forestillingen i mange forskellige scener/kostumer og roller/funktioner. Flere fra ensemblet har replik(ker) undervejs. √ònsker man at g√• til audition som danser uden at skulle synge eller have replikker i forestillingen, er dette ogs√• muligt. Inden for dans er ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù en af de musicals med det bredeste felt af genrer, lige fra Las Vegas- og Broadway-showdans til cancan, disco, folkedans, jazzballet, cheerleading og step samt meget mere, og derudover byder koreografierne p√• uendeligt mange komiske indslag og vinkler. Vi gl√¶der os derfor at se mange st√¶rke dansere til audition, uanset om man har erfaring eller ej inden for de individuelle genrer. G√•r man til audition inden for sang og bliver udtaget til koret blandt rollerne/ensemblet, synger man med p√• mange af de 24 numre i forestillingen ud over at indg√• i mange af de komiske indslag og scener undervejs.

ANG√ÖENDE ROLLER:
N√•r der √•bnes op for auditiontilmeldinger medio december, kan man l√¶se alt om de individuelle roller i forestillingen samt hvad man skal forberede, hvis man g√•r op p√• en rolle eller som ensemble. G√•r man op til ensemblet udelukkende som danser (uden at ville synge eller have replikker i forestillingen), vil man ikke skulle forberede noget hjemmefra. 

ANG√ÖENDE FORESTILLINGEN:
G√∏r dig klar til et latter-festbrag uden lige og glem alt, hvad du tror du ved om musicals ‚Äì og riddere! "SPAMALOT" er baseret p√• den komiske filmklassiker "Monty Python og de sk√∏re riddere" fra 1975 og kaster dig direkte ind i et vanvittigt middelaldereventyr fyldt med latter, kokosn√∏dder, uendelige forvirringer og totalt meningsl√∏se heltebedrifter! 
Forestillingen f√∏lger Kong Arthur og hans noget alternative Riddere af Det Runde Bord, som begiver sig ud p√• en b√•de farlig, t√•belig og fuldst√¶ndig absurd jagt efter Den Hellige Gral. Undervejs m√∏der de alt fra franske forn√¶rmelser til dansende munke, en dr√¶berkanin, dansenymfer, flyvende k√∏er ‚Äì og ikke mindst en vaske√¶gte musicaldiva med stort D!
Der er satire, sk√∏re jokes samt catchy sange og dansenumre i overflod (hvem kan ikke huske "Always Look on the Bright Side of Life"?) i et festfyrv√¶rkeri af b√•de en hyldest til og parodi af musicalgenren. Det er uforudsigeligt, ufiltreret og helt ustyrligt morsomt. En skaml√∏st vidunderlig teateroplevelse for fans af Broadway-musicals og af Monty Pythons forrygende humor ‚Äì og alle dem, der snart bliver det!
"SPAMALOT" har de seneste tyve √•r haft sin sejrsgang over hele verden og blev efter sin debut p√• Broadway i 2005 nomineret til hele 14 Tony-priser og vandt blandt andet for √Örets Bedste Musical. Det bliver med garanti en uforglemmelig og ridderligt underholdende sommer i 2026 ‚Äì for b√•de publikum og de medvirkende!
Nyborg Voldspils ops√¶tning af ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù er den f√∏rste udend√∏rsopf√∏rsel af forestillingen p√• Fyn nogensinde og instrueres af Rasmus Mansachs, der tidligere har instrueret de to ‚ÄùVi maler byen r√∏d: The Musical‚Äù-ops√¶tninger i henholdsvis 2021 og 2025. K√∏b billetter til ‚ÄùSPAMALOT‚Äù allerede nu her: nyborgvoldspil.dk

AUDITIONTILMELDING:
Der √•bnes op for tilmeldinger medio december 2025. Audition finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026. Det vil blive meldt ud p√• Nyborg Voldspils Facebook- og Instagram-profiler, s√• snart man kan tilmelde sig og l√¶se mere om de individuelle roller, ensemblet og selve pr√∏veplanen. Vi ses til auditon! 

Nyborg Voldspil pr√¶senterer:

items.text:
Hello all,

I'm new to this group, just thought I'd introduce myself - I am a location sound recordist with almost a decade of experience, with bases in Somerset and Surrey as well as an extensive list of professional equipment. I'm currently free until about mid-Spring next year.

I am currently hoping to offer my services for a particular type of short fan film (unpaid of course) that takes place in the matrix universe - this is simply because its something that I've dreamt about doing for a long time. I also know other professionals in the industry (such as a skilled DOP/camera op) who also is very passionate about the matrix, who also owns some very pro gear and would love to get involved with a project like this too.

Is there anyone on this group that is considering making a project like this? Feel free to get in touch if you are.

Best regards

James

items.text: Hello! I wondered if anyone can help, i am an actor in my graduating year at drama school looking for temporary work over christmas. I used to work in a pub all year round but i need something that i can pick up and put down due to committments of my training. what do other actors use to find work? or does anyone know any event staff/ waitressing/ bar staff agencies that are good at finding work? many thanks!

topComments.text: I've been doing extra work, the people I work with are very flexible and you get to be on set and meet people in the industry

I'm helping a Chinese production company cast performers for a short-form Douyin (TikTok China) series filming in Cambridge UK. The project is simple, natural and focuses on everyday interactions between people from different backgrounds.

We‚Äôre looking for young male and female performers who can play natural versions of themselves ‚Äî no heavy acting required.

‚ú® **What We‚Äôre Looking For**

Gender: Male & Female

Playing age: 20‚Äì30

Ethnicity: Caucasian

Language: Fluent English (any accent is fine, as long as it‚Äôs clear)

Comfortable acting naturally on camera

Able to follow simple scripts + light improvisation

Based in Cambridge preferred, but London/nearby areas welcome (travel covered)

**üé¨ Production Details**

Location: Cambridge, UK

Usage: Douyin (China‚Äôs TikTok)

Shoot Duration: Half-day or full-day depending on the episode

Schedule: Flexible / ongoing filming

Pay: ¬£30‚Äì¬£60 per hour (depending on experience)

Travel: Covered (if coming from London/nearby)

Food: Provided

Non-broadcast, social media series

üìÑ **About the Project**

A series of short, down-to-earth scenes showing everyday encounters between people from different backgrounds living in the UK. Performers will essentially play themselves ‚Äî relaxed, natural and conversational.

**üì© How to Apply**

Please send me a DM or email me at sanan282000@gmail.com

**CASTING CALL: LIVE SHOW HOSTS**

Los Angeles (Hollywood Studio)

**Firework** is seeking energetic, camera-ready **Live Show Hosts** to lead interactive livestream product demonstrations!

**PAY:** $25-$40/hour (based on experience)

**ROLE DETAILS:**
* Host live product shows from our Hollywood, CA studio
* Present tech & lifestyle products in an authentic, conversational style
* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee
* Average 5-10 hours/week (rarely exceeds 15 hours)
* Mostly weekdays, 8 AM - 8 PM PT

**WE'RE LOOKING FOR:**
* Strong on-camera presence & natural speaking ability
* Reliable, punctual, professional
* Available weekdays during business hours
* Prior hosting/livestream/UGC/acting experience preferred but not required

**AUDITION OPTIONS:**

**Option 1: On-Site Audition**
* Dates: December 10-11, 2025
* Time: 10 AM - 1 PM PT
* 10-15 min audition (3-min one-take hosting scenario)

**Option 2: Self-Tape Submission**
* Deadline: December 11, 2025 (11:59 PM PT)
* 3 minutes, vertical, one continuous take
* Host any tech/electronic product as if live
* Email to: Kimmy@fireworkhq.com
* Subject: [Your Name] ‚Äì Live Show Host Submission - LA Digital Showroom Host - Self Tape Submission

items.text:
Now casting couples in mixed orientation relationships for a new documentary series with a major cable network.

Mixed orientation relationships, often known as lavender partnerships, involve two partners who differ in their sexual orientation. We want to hear from couples who live together, share a daily life, and are engaged, married, or soon to be engaged.

This series will explore how couples navigate identity, commitment, outside expectations, and the realities of loving in a way that challenges societal norms.

If this describes you or someone you know, you can share your story at the link below.

mixedorientationcasting.castingcrane.com

Short film

'he lives here' 

A sleepless corporate worker is forced to confront the monstrous embodiment of their childhood trauma during a terrifying sleep paralysis episode.

A vocalist is needed to compliment the soundtrack for a short film.

Feminine-leaning vocals rooted in harmonising dreamy soundscapes, singing and soft spoken word. 

Inspiration: 

Phoebe Bridgers
Agnes Obel
Ethel Cain 

PLEASE NOTE:
This is a Manchester, UK based opportunity only

üé• Film: Blackbird | Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs Fan Film
üì¢ LAST CALL ‚Äì Letzte M√∂glichkeit, sich zu melden!
‚è∞ Wann?
10.01.2026
Eine √úbernachtung am 10.01. ist selbstverst√§ndlich m√∂glich.
üí∏ Gage: 100 ‚Ç¨
‚ùó Fahrtkosten und Verpflegung sind nicht enthalten, da das Projekt komplett privat finanziert wird.
Die √úbernachtung wird jedoch √ºbernommen.
üìç Wo?
N√∂rdlingen, Landkreis Donau-Ries
üé≠ Wer?
Rolle: Sam (3 Szenen)
Gesucht wird eine Schauspielerin (18‚Äì35 Jahre) mit sehr gutem oder akzentfreiem Englisch und einem jugendlichen Erscheinungsbild (die Charaktere sind Teenager).
Idealerweise mit F√ºhrerschein, da ich leider schlechte Erfahrungen mit Drehtagen und Bahnverbindungen gemacht habe. Falls es anders nicht geht, kann ich mir dar√ºber noch Gedanken machen.
üßç‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Kurzbeschreibung der Rolle ‚ÄûSam‚Äú:
Sam ist ein ganz normales, freundliches Teenager-M√§dchen, das viel lacht, offen ist und es liebt, in die Kamera zu sprechen.
üé¨ Kurze Beschreibung zum Projekt:
Nole und Sam m√ºssen f√ºr ein Schulprojekt einen Kurzfilm drehen. Doch das Kost√ºm von Blackbird erwacht zum Leben und beginnt, die beiden gnadenlos zu verfolgen.
Der Film wird auch im Lost-&-Found-Footage-Stil gedreht.
üí° √úber mich:
Ich bin ein noch sehr unerfahrener, fast schon amateurhafter Filmemacher und habe bisher vier kurze Filme auf meinem YouTube-Kanal ver√∂ffentlicht.
Wenn ihr nach gro√üen Projekten f√ºr euer Portfolio sucht, ist das hier vermutlich nicht das Richtige.
Das Drehbuch ist bereits fertig und ich zeige es euch gerne bei Interesse.

Da es um Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs geht und die Fanbase sehr gro√ü ist, hoffe ich dennoch, dass der Film viele Klicks bekommen wird ‚Äì es bleibt aber klar ein Hobbyprojekt.
Der fertige Film wird auf YouTube ver√∂ffentlicht.

üëâ Ich freue mich sehr auf eure Nachrichten! üòÉ

Tonight and tomorrow only at No Square Theatre in Laguna Beach!

Get your tickets at: [https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804](https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExdE9CMUlNdmlWaHQ1Z0hXRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkDzUxNDc3MTU2OTIyODA2MQABHhigjsOFZIS1vnXu10jY_YsHWJ5nXvz5lgiqWRc5_TvZ_pxZxMayZs6Vc-tX_aem_Qgp-5aGk8mHoi59iA-L5bQ)

SHE KILLS MONSTERS: YOUNG ADVENTURERS EDITION, a play by Qui Nguyen and directed by No Square Theatre Artistic Director, Joe Lauderdale, tells the story of high schooler Agnes Evans as she deals with the death of her younger sister, Tilly. When Agnes finds Tilly‚Äôs Dungeons & Dragons notebook, she gets pulled into an exciting adventure in the imaginary world that was her sister‚Äôs escape. The story is a thrilling, fast-paced dramatic comedy laden with homicidal fairies, nasty ogres, and ‚Äô90s pop culture celebrating both the geek and the warrior inside all of us.

November 22 & 23 Only!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL!**

Hello everyone! My name is Sofia Vargas and I‚Äôm the Producer for the UNCSA third year film, *Metanoia*. We are casting our lead characters!

Story: On the last night of Mariana‚Äôs visit to her brother Mateo in the U.S., the two Latin American siblings are pushed into unfamiliar territory when a moment of discovery at a Latin club gives Mariana a glimpse of who she truly is. Together, they navigate the fragile, unspoken shifts in identity, desire, and growing up that both pull them apart and draw them closer.

We are accepting auditions submissions! Character Breakdowns are attached. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for these roles, send your **name, age, pronouns,** **headshot, and role preference  **to [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com) for audition materials! 

The **interest deadline **is December 1st! 

Production title: Metanoia 

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union 

Paid / Not Paid: Not Paid

Production Type: Student Film

Production Company: University of North Carolina School of the Arts (School of Filmmaking)

Director: Mart√≠n Collo Sastoque 

Producer: Sofia Vargas

Audition Type: In Person Auditions

Filming: January and February 2026

Shooting Location: Winston-Salem, NC

Email: [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com)

We look forward to seeing your audition!

Sharing on behalf of BetweenGigs Casting!!

New Hampshire Casting Call for Union & Non-Union Actors!!

Casting is NOT restricted to New England!! 

Casting for a Sci-Fi trailer.

Casting two actors for a proof-of-concept trailer for an episodic sci-fi thriller. It will be shot at the state of the art Studio Lab facility in Derry NH in mid January. This is a paid gig. Both union and non union talent may submit. A Travel/Lodging budget is available, should talent cast be from outside the New England market.

Please see the details below and submit your materials to casting@humanoriginals.com by end of day Sunday, November 23. Please include contact information for your agent or manager if you have one.

************
Project Title: Resonance: Earth 101
Project Type: Proof-of-Concept Trailer
Union: SAG-AFTRA (Micro-Budget Agreement Pending): Roles are open to both union & non union actors.
Production Company: HumanOriginals
Usage: Online, and client/investor/distributer presentations

Shoot Dates: Two days. Tentatively scheduled for January 13 & 14 2026

Shoot Location: Studio Lab, Derry NH

Fit Date/Table Read: TBD. A stipend will be available
Tech Rehearsal Dates (1-2): TBD. A stipend will be available
Travel Stipend/Lodging: TBD, depending on talent's travel distance.

Shoot/Usage Compensation: $1,000/day per talent.
Meals, credit, and copy will also be provided.

SYNOPSIS
Resonance: Earth 101 is a sci-fi thriller proof-of-concept trailer.

Shortly after crashing on Earth in 1983, Kara discovers a mysterious VHS tape in an abandoned warehouse. This triggers a recorded message from Josh, a Brooklyn teen who seems to know her story, even before they‚Äôve met. Through his nervous humor, warnings about Earth, and a mixtape he calls ‚ÄúEarth 101", Josh offers Kara both survival tools and an unexpected connection.

ROLES
JOSH
‚Ä¢ Male, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A hidden tech prodigy from 1983 Brooklyn ‚Äî sharp, curious, and socially awkward, hiding brilliance behind sarcasm. Nervous yet magnetic. He risks everything to help Kara find her way on Earth.

KARA
‚Ä¢ Female, 18‚Äì25, Black or Mixed Ethnicity
‚Ä¢ A resilient and observant young woman carrying a maturity beyond her years. Athletic and graceful, Kara looks both innocent and ancient, as though she‚Äôs already written into myth. Her arrival on Earth sets off an unexpected chain of events.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS
To be considered for an audition, please email headshot (or current photo), resume, and reel (if available) to casting@humanoriginals.com.

Subject Line of your email should read: Role name / Your name

Submissions are requested by 5:00pm Sunday, November 23. 

If selected to audition, instructions & script for a self-taped audition will be sent to you.

Callbacks, if needed, will be via Zoom.

items.text:
Hi Everyone! I run a nonprofit that provides children who have lost a parent or sibling with a special gift or experience to help them on their grief journey. In June 2026 we are hosting a 5-day free theater day-camp in Boulder for these bereaved children. We are partnering with an Atlanta-based theater company, Destination Theatre. If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

items.text:
Casting call: Digital spot for RV Rental Company 

Looking for talent for an RV Rental shoot on Monday 12/1 OR Tuesday 12/2  in TBD Greater Denver area (within 1 hr)

Looking for a couple (ages ~28-40) with a dog, OR a couple with one young kid (~1-6yo). 

Simple lifestyle scenes around an RV/camping. No lines. 

Rate: $1200 total for the group. 

6 hrs max, likely Noon-6pm. 

If you are interested, please email me (rileyjhanlon@gmail.com) with a group shot (preferred) or individual pics to show everyone, and whether you are available for Monday 12/1, Tuesday 12/2, or both and put ‚ÄúRV Spot - (your name)‚Äù in the subject. 

Thank you!

topComments.text: Jaelyn Bennett I feel like you guys would be perfect for this.  Even if youre on the young side of the age group!
I just submitted!  We would love to do this!
